I think there are additional factors.<br>
<br>
1.   They have an obligation to their customer base to fix existing bugs and to deliver what was promised to the customers for each release. aka Luclin etc.<br>
<br>
2.   Notice EQ getting more laggy?  You do know that every time they add zones they dont add more servers right?  They stack zones on the same cluster of servers. aka ToV with Cabalis, Sebelis with HS etc.  Do you really think they add another 20 sparc 450s everytime they add a zone ?  I think not.<br>
<br>
3.   The quality of the server is going down each week with every patch. If they increase the cash we pay then they should be using this money to increase performance.  However, it appears Verant are trying to keep customers as best they can and are cought in a catch 22 situation - add new zones (aka keep 60s intereted)  - but that needs cash/development or fix bugs/performance issues - which also requires cash development.  The things stopping them from doing this now is the fact that the Corporate world and their shareholders want their dividents to increase and not decrease.  Basically that line graph needs to go up not down.  Basically VI are probably doing a shit job of cashflow management.<br>
<br>
Summary:<br>
I personally am not too bothered about the extra cash however I think its quite poor timing of them considering the fuxored zones, quests, performance and SoL undelivered elements.<br>
<br>
Majouth<br>
